WEBVTT

00:03.256 --> 00:06.358
<i>- Maura: It all just happened so fast.
- Jane: Stay here.</i>

00:06.393 --> 00:08.194
- I don't want to spook him.
- Jane.

00:08.228 --> 00:09.428
No, I know this guy well enough
to know he's not bluffing.

00:09.463 --> 00:10.529
Be careful!

00:10.564 --> 00:11.530
- You know Jane.
- Paul.

00:11.565 --> 00:14.233
<i>She never quits. She was determined
to talk him off the bridge.</i>

00:14.267 --> 00:15.434
Listen to me, okay?

00:15.469 --> 00:17.236
- You're wasting your time.
- No. No.

00:17.270 --> 00:19.004
Just ... just listen.

00:19.039 --> 00:20.406
<i>She told him she didn't believe
he killed his girlfriend.</i>

00:20.440 --> 00:22.174
Jane, don't.

00:22.209 --> 00:23.642
<i>She was sure he was set up</i>

00:23.677 --> 00:27.079
<i>and they needed to bring
the real killer to justice.</i>

00:27.114 --> 00:30.116
- Come on.
- But then he slipped.

00:30.150 --> 00:31.517
- Whoa.
- No!

00:31.551 --> 00:33.552
Ah!
[Water splashes]

00:34.287 --> 00:37.713
Jane!

00:37.748 --> 00:40.426
Jane!
Jane!!

00:42.162 --> 00:43.195
[Siren wails]

00:43.230 --> 00:46.532
I should've stopped her.
[Helicopter blades whirring]

00:46.566 --> 00:50.636
There's nothing you could do, huh?

00:50.670 --> 00:52.138
Still no sign of them?

00:52.172 --> 00:53.372
Another coast guard
boat joined the search.

00:53.406 --> 00:56.208
- You heard from the harbor patrol?
- They got divers in the water.

00:56.243 --> 00:58.310
But she won't survive very
long in this cold water.

00:58.345 --> 00:59.712
I got to get on one of those boats.

00:59.746 --> 01:01.247
No, there's nothing
you can do on the water.

01:01.281 --> 01:03.282
We need to continue
coordinating the search,

01:03.316 --> 01:05.351
relaying information from here.

01:05.385 --> 01:07.119
Maura, did you see which
way they were swimming?

01:07.154 --> 01:09.221
No. The current just swept them
away from the bridge so fast,

01:09.256 --> 01:11.056
they just disappeared in the darkness.

01:11.091 --> 01:14.004
You know the currents around
here. What are their chances?

01:14.528 --> 01:17.363
Come on, Korsak. I really need
to know where we stand here.

01:17.397 --> 01:18.731
People have gone in
the water around here

01:18.765 --> 01:21.467
and been swept right out to sea.
But they weren't Jane Rizzoli.

01:21.501 --> 01:24.603
- I can't believe I let her jump.
- You didn't let her.

01:25.138 --> 01:26.672
Their best chance is if they were able

01:26.706 --> 01:28.340
to swim to one of these
outlying islands here.

01:28.375 --> 01:29.341
[Cellphone ringing]

01:30.026 --> 01:31.560
Korsak.

01:31.594 --> 01:32.861
[Police radio chatter]

01:32.896 --> 01:36.899
- Oh. Okay, thanks.
- What is it?

01:36.933 --> 01:38.967
The press. They know we're
searching for Jane and Paul,

01:39.002 --> 01:40.836
want to know what's going on.

01:40.870 --> 01:42.471
Prosecutor jumps off a bridge
after killing his girlfriend?

01:42.505 --> 01:43.605
That's a front-page story.

01:43.640 --> 01:46.675
Someone needs to notify Paul's
wife before the press gets to her.

01:46.710 --> 01:48.777
Well, we'll stay here
until they find her.

01:48.812 --> 01:53.248
I'll be back asap.
Let me know if you hear anything.

